# StudyHard Repository Reference (Complete Inventory)

This document summarizes every tracked project file (excluding dependency/build output folders such as `node_modules` and `.next`).
For each item: what it does, where it is used, and why it exists.

## Root Files

- `.env`: Environment placeholder file (includes Builder key placeholder). Used by runtime when env vars are loaded. Needed to keep env contract explicit.
- `.env.local`: Local development env values (Supabase URL/key). Used by `lib/supabase.ts` and `lib/supabase/server.ts`. Needed for local auth/database connectivity.
- `.gitignore`: Ignore rules for generated artifacts/deps. Used by Git. Needed to keep repo clean.
- `eslint.config.mjs`: ESLint setup (Next + TS rules). Used by `npm run lint`. Needed for static quality checks.
- `next-env.d.ts`: Next.js-generated TypeScript typing entry. Used by TS compiler. Needed for Next type support.
- `next.config.ts`: Next app config (currently minimal/default). Used by Next build/runtime. Needed as extension point for future runtime/build tuning.
- `package-lock.json`: Exact dependency lock graph. Used by npm install/CI. Needed for reproducible installs.
- `package.json`: Scripts + deps (`next`, `react`, Supabase, Vitest, Tailwind, dnd-kit). Used by npm tooling. Needed for project lifecycle.
- `postcss.config.mjs`: PostCSS pipeline with Tailwind plugin. Used by CSS build. Needed to compile Tailwind styles.
- `proxy.ts`: Auth/session middleware-like request gate using Supabase SSR cookie sync; redirects protected routes. Used by Next request pipeline. Needed for route protection + onboarding enforcement.
- `README.md`: High-level app overview, setup, architecture notes. Used by contributors. Needed for onboarding/handoff.
- `tsconfig.json`: TypeScript strict compile config and `@/*` path alias. Used by TS/IDE/build. Needed for type safety and import consistency.
- `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo`: TS incremental cache file. Used by TypeScript incremental mode. Needed for faster rebuilds.
- `UiUX.md`: UI/UX implementation notes and design behavior reference. Used by design/development workflow. Needed for UI consistency.
- `vitest.config.ts`: Unit test configuration (node env, setup file, alias). Used by `npm test`. Needed to run tests with project path aliases.
- `vitest.setup.ts`: Global test bootstrap (Next cache mocks, timezone). Used by Vitest before tests. Needed so server-action tests run outside real Next runtime.

## CI and Editor

- `.github/workflows/ci.yml`: CI pipeline (typecheck, lint, tests, build). Used by GitHub Actions on push/PR. Needed to prevent regressions.
- `.vscode/settings.json`: Workspace editor settings. Used by VS Code. Needed for consistent local tooling behavior.

## App Root

- `app/favicon.ico`: Browser tab icon. Used by Next app metadata routing. Needed for branding/usability.
- `app/globals.css`: Global Tailwind + CSS variables/tokens. Used by root layout. Needed as visual design foundation.
- `app/layout.tsx`: Global app shell (fonts/providers/theme/toast wrappers). Used by all routes. Needed to share app-wide context.
- `app/page.tsx`: Root route redirect logic (auth-aware). Used at `/`. Needed to route users into login/dashboard quickly.

